          "content": "Bonjour !\n\nHere is a basic Arduino code to get you started:\n```c++\nvoid setup() {\n  // Initialize digital pin 13 as an output\n  pinMode(13, OUTPUT);\n}\n\nvoid loop() {\n  // Turn the LED on\n  digitalWrite(13, HIGH);\n  delay(1000); // Wait for 1 second\n\n  // Turn the LED off\n  digitalWrite(13, LOW);\n  delay(1000); // Wait for 1 second\n}\n```\nThis code sets up digital pin 13 as an output and then blinks the built-in LED on and off at a rate of one second.\n\nNote: This is just a simple example to get you started. You can modify it or add more code to create your own projects!\n\nWhat would you like to do next?",
